results.name: Number of subgroups of the group C_n X C_n X C_n (where C_n is the cyclic group of order n).
comment: For a prime p: a(p) = 2*(p^2+p+2). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Oct 22 2001
link: Mario Hampejs and László Tóth, On the subgroups of finite Abelian groups of rank three, Annales Univ. Sci. Budapest., Sect. Comp. 39 (2013) 111-124.
